[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Investigating Maven Annotations and Class Loading**\n\nI'm trying to complete the Antlr4 class and examine the method body. It seems that javac doesn't necessarily read method code for type checking. A potential issue with Maven annotations (`org.apache.maven.plugins.annotations.Parameter`) arises, especially if class loading depends on these annotations. \n\nIf the runtime class lacks an annotation, the JVM might ignore it. I need to consider whether the native image analysis can scan these annotations. Also, I wonder if the `FormatterStep.format(String, File)` method can return null if there's no change? I'll need to clarify that with the Spotless FormatterStep convention.\n\n**Verifying Formatter Steps**\n\nI'm looking to verify if the Trim step returns the original string when unchanged. It seems that if the input changes, it returns the updated string, and it handles end newlines well. \n\nHowever, there's a potential issue with the `PipeStepPair` test. If `trimTrailingWhitespace.format(protectedInput)` returns null, that could indicate something's off. Also, I wonder if `EndWithNewline.format` can return null when the string already has a newline. Some functions might return null if there's no change, but I think the Spotless FormatterStep `format` should always return a formatted string. I might need to inspect the source code and possibly download the spotless-lib sources for a closer look.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0bd1e09e4d4628da0169fe2e7abc448195b7419f710d2199a4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_i6LC49FsW-as1G6yl6Jq8M_d1t80bcwgpbBSDAAsB5xh4KDRN-cKfmfnYEfHpHP_h8hUciVQXCH62JLHJdPHJXBv-hltzOrlmGRWiaSxnrqsvM1wK_RLxrFaijhelgHpMr97UdHakI5yJnyUugOdLJHvqmwE-drihtf1YcGZNoEsm9O7Id-IPxJuk_sNWJND3H4cOj7UEjIJhm3IgkhDcJonqL5tUxUunFwVz3IhhPO-q47KfGU3Sd-V4XbVTAwDaugD3LHWmiS4P9hlQEctoWgrWkEdYtLoqroZxodqLbAHoYPmqkrGKoQnPNrM8k2ij0z