REqzJLbuSOndKRfx5qcCunN_WTZL4JaEN8zfnkYYxPxDXjLIbe3JsLcU4QVogk5gOBdEPN6BXPwkYUP8CvYYsg6MU7zZ95VH8Cu--50wU10r1aJh4B8Nv19QxBS9hg9gbcwhV6H8Sdnhb1zQkVFlnArvhoiIFIJfvSU-zlMdR-91_CKinWRmaAcBEyV1Xo-Tc5cUYtkNizgFH5KLc_6TyD4ZFMDGNFEtAePZwt2cN_hw3jU1qR8g5QJJiIqBdWyzajYcYAb0N9gNLOTHBjnxZDqyk64VFx8LMPOxA5_YG9lKyRBTNGO55L8N6oluj1Eq80Z6rqksZ-NK1m8QgU_TgK-0Qo1RgrRTV8ETAw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating Maven Annotations and Class Loading**\\n\\nI'm trying to complete the Antlr4 class and examine the method body. It seems that javac doesn't necessarily read method code for type checking. A potential issue with Maven annotations (`org.apache.maven.plugins.annotations.Parameter`) arises, especially if class loading depends on these annotations. \\n\\nIf the runtime class lacks an annotation, the JVM might ignore it. I need to consider whether the native image analysis can scan these annotations. Also, I wonder if the `FormatterStep.format(String, File)` method can return null if there's no change? I'll need to clarify that with the Spotless FormatterStep convention.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Verifying Formatter Steps**\\n\\nI'm looking to verify if the Trim step returns the original string when unchanged. It seems that if the input changes, it returns the updated string, and it handles end newlines well. \\n\\nHowever, there's a potential issue with the `PipeStepPair` test. If `trimTrailingWhitespace.format(protectedInput)` returns null, that could indicate something's off. Also, I wonder if `EndWithNewline.format` can return null when the string already has a newline. Some functions might return null if there's no change, but I think the Spotless FormatterStep `format` should always return a formatted string. I might need to inspect the source code and possibly download the spotless-lib sources for a closer look.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Okh6l5HctmXZ0z1psYmlQlNi|fc_0bd1e09e4d4628da0169fe2e8ba0e48195aab1e4ae3a092099", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, pathlib, zipfile\nout=pathlib.Path('/home/vjovanov/tmp/spotless/spotless-lib-2.45.0-sources.jar')\nurllib.request.urlretrieve('https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/diffplug/spotless/spotless-lib/2.45.0/spotless-lib-2.45.0-sources.jar', out)\nwith zipfile.ZipFile(out) as z:\n    for name in ['com/diffplug/spotless/generic/TrimTrailingWhitespaceStep.java','com/diffplug/spotless/generic/EndWithNewlineStep.java','com/diffplug/spotless/generic/PipeStepPair.java','com/diffplug/spotless/FormatterStep.java']:\n        print('---', name)\n        print(z.read(name).decode()[:3000])\nPY", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1061, "output": 1070, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51795, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778265718942, "responseId": "resp_0bd1e09e4d4628da0169fe2e797cc0819593019734a26afd40"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Okh6l5HctmXZ0z1psYmlQlNi|fc_0bd1e09e4d4628da0169fe2e8ba0e48195aab1e4ae3a092099", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "--- com/diffplug/spotless/generic/TrimTrailingWhitespaceStep.java\n/*\n * Copyright 2016 DiffPlug\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n *     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage com.diffplug.spotless.generic;\n\nimport com.diffplug.spotless.FormatterStep;\n\npublic final class TrimTrailingWhitespaceStep {\n\t// prevent direct instantiation\n\tprivate TrimTrailingWhitespaceStep() {}\n\n\tpublic static FormatterStep create() {\n\t\treturn ReplaceRegexStep.create(\"trimTrailingWhitespace\", \"[ \\t]+$\", \"\");\n\t}\n}\n\n--- com/diffplug/spotless/generic/EndWithNewlineStep.java\n/*\n * Copyright 2016 DiffPlug\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n *     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage com.diffplug.spotless.generic;\n\nimport com.diffplug.spotless.FormatterStep;\n\npublic final class EndWithNewlineStep {\n\t// prevent direct instantiation\n\tprivate EndWithNewlineStep() {}\n\n\t/** Creates a FormatterStep which forces lines to end with a newline. */\n\tpublic static FormatterStep create() {\n\t\treturn FormatterStep.create(\"endWithNewline\",\n\t\t\t\tEndWithNewlineStep.class,\n\t\t\t\tunused -> EndWithNewlineStep::format);\n\t}\n\n\tprivate static String format(String rawUnix) {\n\t\t// simplifies the logic below if we can assume length > 0\n\t\tif (rawUnix.isEmpty()) {\n\t\t\treturn \"\\n\";\n\t\t}\n\n\t\t// find the last character which has real content\n\t\tint lastContentCharacter = rawUnix.length() - 1;\n\t\tchar c;\n\t\twhile (lastContentCharacter >= 0) {\n\t\t\tc = rawUnix.charAt(lastContentCharacter);\n\t\t\tif (c == '\\n' || c == '\\t' || c == ' ') {\n\t\t\t\t--lastContentCharacter;\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tbreak;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\t// if it's already clean, no need to create another string\n\t\tif (lastContentCharacter == -1) {\n\t\t\treturn \"\\n\";\n\t\t} else if (lastContentCharacter == rawUnix.length() - 2 && rawUnix.charAt(rawUnix.length() - 1) == '\\n') {\n\t\t\treturn rawUnix;\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tStringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder(lastContentCharacter + 2);\n\t\t\tbuilder.append(rawUnix, 0, lastContentCharacter + 1);\n\t\t\tbuilder.append('\\n');\n\t\t\treturn builder.toString();\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\n--- com/diffplug/spotless/generic/PipeStepPair.java\n/*\n * Copyright 2020-2021 DiffPlug\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n *     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage com.diffplug.spotless.generic;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Collection;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Objects;\nimport java.util.regex.Matcher;\nimport java.util.regex.Pattern;\n\nimport com.diffplug.spotless.Formatter;\nimport com.diffplug.spotless.FormatterFunc;\nimport com.diffplug.spotless.FormatterStep;\nimport com.diffplug.spotless.LineEnding;\n\nimport edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.SuppressFBWarnings;\n\npublic class PipeStepPair {\n\t/** The two steps will be named {@code <name>In} and {@code <name>Out}. */\n\tpublic static Builder named(String name) {\n\t\treturn new Builder(name);\n\t}\n\n\tpublic static String defaultToggleName() {\n\t\treturn \"toggle\";\n\t}\n\n\tpublic static String defaultTog